-d'Or, Bourgogne-Franche-Comté, Frankrig"},"nl":{"Abt 1189–21 January 1241":"circa 1189–21 januari 1241","1190–1239":"1190–1239","1211–1255":"1211–1255","1215–1275":"1215–1275","1189–1241":"1189–1241","1190":"1190","30 November 1239":"30 november 1239","21 January 1241":"21 januari 1241","1275":"1275","1241":"1241","ABT 1215":"circa 1215","28 January 1241":"28 januari 1241","1239":"1239","1215":"1215","Abt 1189":"circa 1189","Abt 1211":"circa 1211","1189":"1189","1255":"1255","1211":"1211","1210":"1210","Til-Châtel, Dijon, Côte-d'Or, Bourgogne-Franche-Comté, France":"Dijon, Côte-d'Or, Bourgogne-Franche-Comté, Frankrijk","Coublanc, Langres, Haute-Marne, Grand Est, France":"Coublanc, Haute-Marne, Grand Est, Frankrijk","Til-Châtel, Côte-d'Or, Bourgogne-Franche-Comté, France":"Til-Châtel, Côte-d'Or, Bourgogne-Franche-Comté, Frankrijk"},"en":{"Abt 1189–21 January 1241":"about 1189–21 January 1241","1190–1239":"1190–1239","1211–1255":"1211–1255","1215–1275":"1215–1275","1189–1241":"1189–1241","1190":"1190","30 November 1239":"30 November 1239","21 January 1241":"21 January 1241","1275":"1275","1241":"1241","ABT 1215":"about 1215","28 January 1241":"28 January 1241","1239":"1239","1215":"1215","Abt 1189":"about 1189","Abt 1211":"about 1211","1189":"1189","1255":"1255","1211":"1211","1210":"1210","Til-Châtel, Dijon, Côte-d'Or, Bourgogne-Franche-Comté, France":"Dijon, Côte-d'Or, Bourgogne-Franche-Comté, France","Coublanc, Langres, Haute-Marne, Grand Est, France":"Coublanc, Haute-Marne, Grand Est, France","Til-Châtel, Côte-d'Or, Bourgogne-Franche-Comté, France":"Til-Châtel, Côte-d'Or, Bourgogne-Franche-Comté, France","nameMeanings":[{"name":"De","type":"LAST","attribution":"Dictionary of American Family Names © Patrick Hanks 2003, 2006.","meanings":["Some characteristic forenames:  Indian Dilip, Anirban, Gopal, Alok, Anindya, Arunava, Asit, Asok, Dibyendu, Goutam, Indra, Indranil.","Indian: variant of   Dey  ."],"variants":[{"name":"Dey","meanings":["Some characteristic forenames:  Indian Ashit, Indu, Naina, Partha, Soumya, Ajit, Anjan, Anjana, Anup, Arjun, Arun, Ashim.","English, Scottish, and Welsh: variant of   Day  .","German: topographic name from a field name in North Rhine-Westphalia, denoting a sizeable piece of land, from Middle Low German <i>dē</i> ‘thigh’ (referring to the shape of the property)."]}]},{"name":"Til","type":"LAST","attribution":"Dictionary of American Family Names © Patrick Hanks 2003, 2006.","meanings":["Some characteristic forenames:  Cambodian Yoeum, Chheang, Noeun, Phoeun, Sambath, Soeun, Sokhom, Sombath, Sovann.  Southeast Asian Lach, Mau, Sophal, Thong, Thy, Leng, Roeun.","German, Dutch, and English: variant of   Timm  .","Cambodian: written ទឹម, corresponding to the Khmer word meaning ‘to yoke animals’."],"variants":[{"name":"Timm","meanings":["Some characteristic forenames:  German Otto, Erwin, Ewald, Helmuth, Irmgard, Ernst, Frieda, Angelika, Arno, Bernhard, Bernhardt, Dieter.","English (Yorkshire and Lincolnshire): from the Middle English pal name <i>Timme</i>, which also gave rise to   Timson  . It may be a survival of an unrecorded Old English personal name, <i>Tima</i>, of uncertain origin. See also   Timms  .","North German and Dutch: from a short form of the personal name <i>Dietmar</i> (see   Dittmar  )."]},{"name":"Tims","meanings":["Dutch: patronymic from the personal name   Tim   or   Timm  .","English (Oxfordshire): variant of   Timms  ."]}]},{"name":"Chatel","type":"LAST","attribution":"Dictionary of American Family Names © Patrick Hanks 2003, 2006.","meanings":["Some characteristic forenames:  French Celine, Emile, Gilles, Jacques, Lucien.","French (also <b>Châtel</b>):","habitational name from (Le) Chatel or (Le) Châtel, names of several places in various parts of France, from Old French <i>chastel</i> ‘castle, fortified building’."],"variants":[{"name":"Chateau","meanings":["Some characteristic forenames:  French Thierry, Francois, Michel.","French (<b>Château</b>):","from Old French <i>chastel</i> (French <i>château</i>) ‘castle, fortified building’, a topographic name for someone who lived in or near a castle, or a metonymic occupational name for someone who worked in one."]}]},{"name":"Guy","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["From an Old French name, of Germanic (Frankish) origin, originally a short form of a compound name starting with <i>witu</i> ‘wood’ or <i>wīt</i> ‘wide’. This was adopted by the Normans and introduced by them to England. In Old French initial <i>w-</i> regularly became <i>gu-</i>. The usual Norman forms of the name were <i>Gy</i> or <i>Guido</i>. In medieval Latin the same name is found as <i>Wido</i>. It was a popular name among the Normans, enhanced no doubt by the romance of Guy of Warwick, recounting the exploits of a folk hero of the Crusades."],"variants":[]},{"name":"II","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["1  ♂ ‘Wondrous’ or ‘enlightenment’.","2  ♀ ‘Fine jade’."],"variants":[]}],"lifeSummary":"Guy II De Til Chatel was born about 1189, in Til-Châtel, Côte-d'Or, Bourgogne-Franche-Comté, France. He married Guillemette de Coublanc in 1210, in Coublanc, Haute-Marne, Grand Est, France. They were the parents of at least 1 son and 1 daughter. He died on 21 January 1241, in his hometown, at the age of 53, and was buried in Til-Châtel, Côte-d'Or, Bourgogne-Franche-Comté, France."},"et":{"Abt 1189–21 January 1241":"umbes 1189–21. jaanuar 1241","1190–1239":"1190–1239","1211–1255":"1211–1255","1215–1275":"1215–1275","1189–1241":"1189–1241","1190":"1190","30 November 1239":"30. november 1239","21 January 1241":"21. jaanuar 1241","1275":"1275","1241":"1241","ABT 1215":"umbes 1215","28 January 1241":"28. jaanuar 1241","1239":"1239","1215":"1215","Abt 1189":"umbes 1189","Abt 1211":"umbes 1211","1189":"1189","1255":"1255","1211":"1211","1210":"1210","Til-Châtel, Dijon, Côte-d'Or, Bourgogne-Franche-Comté, France":"Dijon, Côte-d'Or, Bourgogne-Franche-Comté, Prantsusmaa","Coublanc, Langres, Haute-Marne, Grand Est, France":"Coublanc, Haute-Marne, Grand Est, Prantsusmaa","Til-Châtel, Côte-d'Or, Bourgogne-Franche-Comté, France":"Til-Châtel, Côte-d'Or, Bourgogne-Franche-Comté, Prantsusmaa"},"fi":{"Abt 1189–21 January 1241":"noin 1189–21. tammikuuta 1241","1190–1239":"1190–1239","1211–1255":"1211–1255","1215–1275":"1215–1275","1189–1241":"1189–1241","1190":"1190","30 November 1239":"30. marraskuuta 1239","21 January 1241":"21. tammikuuta 1241","1275":"1275","1241":"1241","ABT 1215":"noin 1215","28 January 1241":"28. tammikuuta 1241","1239":"1239","1215":"1215","Abt 1189":"noin 1189","Abt 1211":"noin 1211","1189":"1189","1255":"1255","1211":"1211","1210":"1210","Til-Châtel, Dijon, Côte-d'Or, Bourgogne-Franche-Comté, France":"Dijon, Côte-d'Or, Bourgogne-Franche-Comté, Ranska","Coublanc, Langres, Haute-Marne, Grand Est, France":"Coublanc, Haute-Marne, Grand Est, Ranska","Til-Châtel, Côte-d'Or, Bourgogne-Franche-Comté, France":"Til-Châtel, Côte-d'Or, Bourgogne-Franche-Comté, Ranska"},"fr":{"Abt 1189–21 January 1241":"environ 1189–21 janvier 1241","1190–1239":"1190–1239","1211–1255":"1211–1255","1215–1275":"1215–1275","1189–1241":"1189–1241","1190":"1190","30 November 1239":"30 novembre 1239","21 January 1241":"21 janvier 1241","1275":"1275","1241":"1241","ABT 1215":"environ 1215","28 January 1241":"28 janvier 1241","1239":"1239","1215":"1215","Abt 1189":"environ 1189","Abt 1211":"environ 1211","1189":"1189","1255":"1255","1211":"1211","1210":"1210","Til-Châtel, Dijon, Côte-d'Or, Bourgogne-Franche-Comté, France":"Dijon, Côte-d'Or, Bourgogne-Franche-Comté, France","Coublanc, Langres, Haute-Marne, Grand Est, France":"Coublanc, Haute-Marne, Grand Est, France","Til-Châtel, Côte-d'Or, Bourgogne-Franche-Comté, France":"Til-Châtel, Côte-d'Or, Bourgogne-Franche-Comté, France","lifeSummary":"Guy II De Til Chatel est né environ 1189, à Til-Châtel, Côte-d'Or, Bourgogne-Franche-Comté, France. Il a épousé Guillemette de Coublanc en 1210, à Coublanc, Haute-Marne, Grand Est, France. Ils ont eu au moins 1 fils et 1 fille. Il est décédé le 21 janvier 1241, dans sa ville natale, à l’âge de 53 ans, et a été enterré à Til-Châtel, Côte-d'Or, Bourgogne-Franche-Comté, France."},"de":{"Abt 1189–21 January 1241":"um 1189–21. Januar 1241","1190–1239":"1190–1239","1211–1255":"1211–1255","1215–1275":"1215–1275","1189–1241":"1189–1241","1190":"1190","30 November 1239":"30. November 1239","21 January 1241":"21. Januar 1241","1275":"1275","1241":"1241","ABT 1215":"um 1215","28 January 1241":"28. Januar 1241","1239":"1239","1215":"1215","Abt 1189":"um 1189","Abt 1211":"um 1211","1189":"1189","1255":"1255","1211":"1211","1210":"1210","Til-Châtel, Dijon, Côte-d'Or, Bourgogne-Franche-Comté, France":"Dijon, Côte-d'Or, Bourgogne-Franche-Comté, Frankreich","Coublanc, Langres, Haute-Marne, Grand Est, France":"Coublanc, Haute-Marne, Großer Osten, Frankreich","Til-Châtel, Côte-d'Or, Bourgogne-Franche-Comté, France":"Til-Châtel, Côte-d'Or, Bourgogne-Franche-Comté, Frankreich","lifeSummary":"Guy II De Til Chatel wurde um 1189 in Til-Châtel, Côte-d'Or, Bourgogne-Franche-Comté, Frankreich geboren. Er hat 1210 in Coublanc, Haute-Marne, Großer Osten, Frankreich Guillemette de Coublanc geheiratet. Sie hatten mindestens 1 Sohn und 1 Tochter. Er starb am 21. Januar 1241 im Alter von 53 Jahren in seinem Geburtsort und wurde in Til-Châtel, Côte-d'Or, Bourgogne-Franche-Comté, Frankreich begraben."},"ht":{"Abt 1189–21 January 1241":"about 1189–21 January 1241","1190–1239":"1190–1239","1211–1255":"1211–1255","1215–1275":"1215–1275","1189–1241":"1189–1241","1190":"1190","30 November 1239":"30 November 1239","21 January 1241":"21 January 1241","1275":"1275","1241":"1241","ABT 1215":"about 1215","28 January 1241":"28 January 1241","1239":"1239","1215":"1215","Abt 1189":"about 1189","Abt 1211":"about 1211","1189":"1189","1255":"1255","1211":"1211","1210":"12